{
  "local_port": 32782,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I connect a non-smart TV with my smartphone?",
  "response": "Connecting a non-smart TV to your smartphone can be done in several ways, depending on the available ports on your TV and your smartphone. Here are some methods:\n\n---\n\n### **1. HDMI Connection**\n   - **What you need**: An HDMI cable, and possibly an HDMI adapter for your phone (depending on the phone's port).\n   - **Steps**:\n     1. Connect your phone to the TV using an HDMI cable. If your phone doesn\u2019t have an HDMI port, use an adapter (e.g., USB-C to HDMI or Lightning to HDMI for iPhones).\n     2. Switch the TV to the correct HDMI input.\n     3. Your phone\u2019s screen will be mirrored on the TV.\n\n---\n\n### **2. MHL (Mobile High-Definition Link)**\n   - **What you need**: An MHL adapter compatible with your phone and an HDMI cable.\n   - **Steps**:\n     1. Connect the MHL adapter to your phone\u2019s charging port.\n     2. Connect the HDMI cable from the adapter to the TV.\n     3. Switch the TV to the correct HDMI input.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Chromecast or Streaming Device**\n   - **What you need**: A Google Chromecast, Roku, or similar streaming device.\n   - **Steps**:\n     1. Plug the streaming device into your TV\u2019s HDMI port.\n     2. Set up the device using your smartphone and Wi-Fi.\n     3. Use the corresponding app (e.g., Google Home for Chromecast) to cast content from your phone to the TV.\n\n---\n\n### **4. USB Connection**\n   - **What you need**: A USB cable and supported media files.\n   - **Steps**:\n     1. Connect your phone to the TV using a USB cable.\n     2. Switch the TV to the USB input.\n     3. Access the files on your phone from the TV\u2019s USB menu (limited to media files).\n\n---\n\n### **5. VGA or AV Cables (Older TVs)**\n   - **What you need**: A VGA/AV adapter for your phone and the appropriate cables.\n   - **Steps**:\n     1. Connect your phone to the TV using the adapter and cables.\n     2. Switch the TV to the correct input.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Screen Mirroring with Miracast**\n   - **What you need**: A Miracast-enabled dongle or receiver.\n   - **Steps**:\n     1. Connect the Miracast dongle to your TV\u2019s HDMI port.\n     2. Enable screen mirroring on your phone (check settings under \u201cCast\u201d or \u201cScreen Mirroring\u201d).\n     3. Connect your phone to the Miracast dongle.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Analog AV (RCA) Connection**\n   - **What you need**: An RCA to 3.5mm adapter for your phone and RCA cables.\n   - **Steps**:\n     1. Connect the RCA cables from the TV to the adapter.\n     2. Plug the adapter into your phone\u2019s headphone jack.\n     3. Switch the TV to the correct input.\n\n---\n\nChoose the method that best suits your TV and phone\u2019s capabilities!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
